I personally use AS for column aliases and don&#039;t use it for tables.

Nice article...&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
The same goes for insert statements&lt;br /&gt;
For example instead of&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
INSERT BLA&lt;br /&gt;
VALUES()&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
I would do&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
INSERT BLA(column list)&lt;br /&gt;
VALUES()&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
that way if they add 2 columns with defaults later on it won&#039;t break any of your code&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Now the question is do you alias like this&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
TableName Alias&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
or&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
TableName AS Alias&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
